Package de.boereck.matcher.helpers

This package contains a set of classes providing static methods to help defining cases and actions for the Case Match library.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TypeCheck<I,O>
    Function checking if an instance of I is either instance of or exactly of type O.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayMatchHelpers
    Provides static helper functions for defining matches in CaseMatchers based on array values.
    CollectionMatchHelpers
    This class provides static helper methods for matching collection objects.
    ComparableMatchHelpers
    This class provides static methods that can be used in defining matches for case matches on Comparable instances.
    ConsumerHelpers
    This class provides static methods that may help with defining consumers of cases in the found case library
    This class is not intended to be instantiated or sub-classed.
    DoubleMatchHelpers
    This class provides static methods and fields that may help with defining consumers of cases in the found case library, helping defining matches for double values.
    IntMatchHelpers
    This class provides static methods and final fields holding references to methods that can be used as predicates in case definitions of matchers for int values.
    LongMatchHelpers
    This class provides static methods and final fields holding references to methods that can be used as predicates in case definitions of matchers for long values.
    MatchHelpers
    This class provides static methods and fields that help with defining matches with CaseMatchers.
    OptionalMatchHelpers
    Provides static helper functions for defining matches in CaseMatchers based on Optional values.
    StringMatchHelpers
    Provides static helper functions for defining matches in CaseMatchers based on String values.

Package de.boereck.matcher.helpers Description

This package contains a set of classes providing static methods to help defining cases and actions for the Case Match library.
